fields.name: AvailabilityZone
fields.description: The value that will be used for machines in this rack to represent the availability zones that can be referenced by Hybrid AKS Clusters for node arrangement.

fields.name: ClusterId
fields.description: The resource ID of the cluster the rack is created for. This value is set when the rack is created by the cluster.

fields.name: DetailedStatus
fields.description: The more detailed status of the rack.

fields.name: DetailedStatusMessage
fields.description: The descriptive message about the current detailed status.

fields.name: ProvisioningState
fields.description: The provisioning state of the rack resource.

fields.name: RackLocation
fields.description: The free-form description of the rack location. (e.g. “DTN Datacenter, Floor 3, Isle 9, Rack 2B”)

fields.name: RackSerialNumber
fields.description: The unique identifier for the rack within Network Cloud cluster. An alternate unique alphanumeric value other than a serial number may be provided if desired.
